{
  "stem": "24409.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Otherwise, everybody will be arrested, and the community will be right in saying that we-- the idea was not to move, not to show.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we didn't do anything in terms of transports.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we did do one thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We took the lists of those who would be ready to go, of these young people, and told them, get a passport.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To get the passport, you have to have a-- young people usually didn't have passports.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they checked whether you didn't owe any taxes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was some delay before you get your passport.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this way, they got their passports, and they brought the passports to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From 9 or 10 years, to 22 or 25 years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [INAUDIBLE] I would say 22 years about. 25 years too high.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I approached them in a rather dramatic interview with Eichmann.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After a few weeks of the German presence in Vienna, where everything was in the open, nobody knows what is going to happen, everybody run to the consulates to get visa, and no consulates gives you entrance visas, they all close their doors to the threatened inflow of refugees, probably without money.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just people without money coming into the country.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one day-- the day should be establishable from the Jewish history of Vienna.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One day, Eichmann, who was in charge of Jewish problems for Vienna, orders all the leaders of the Jewish organizations to come to the office of the Zionist organization, some office of the Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, you know, in Marc-Aurel-Strasse-- it was, I believe, Marc, M-A-R-C, Aurel, A-U-R-E-L, Strasse, he was a Roman emperor who founded Vienna.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And from every group, the people came, as ordered.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were not ordered by names, but it was became known very fast.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
